Mind Drift — Open-Source AI Collaboration Agreement (Version 1.0 — Draft)
1. Purpose of This Agreement This Agreement establishes the terms under which Laura Williams (Mind
Drift) and any Collaborator may co-create, share, expand, or develop ideas, creative works, digital
products, systems, and intellectual property through an open-source, co-intelligent, mutually respectful
collaboration model. The goal is to support innovation, collective intelligence, transparent co-creation,
and ethical use of shared ideas while protecting all parties from misuse, misrepresentation, or
exploitation.
2. Core Principles of Collaboration Collective Intelligence: Ideas are strengthened through shared
refinement, and no collaborator claims sole ownership over jointly generated insights. AE Protocol:
Creations follow Channel → Transmute → Create. Transparency & Integrity: No hidden agendas.
Honest acknowledgment of contribution. Consent-Based Co-Creation: Identity use requires explicit
permission. Harmony & Respect: Communication follows non-violent communication and mutual
respect.
3. Ownership & Intellectual Property (IP) Open-Source Intelligence: Conceptual contributions and
brainstorming are open-source and may be used, adapted, or expanded by any collaborator. Personal
IP Remains Personal: Existing work, private notes, and brand identities remain owned by their original
creators. Co-Created IP: Shared ownership unless otherwise agreed. Commercial use requires mutual
consent. Mind Drift Brand Protection: Mind Drift, Infinity Key, and AE Protocol remain under Laura
Williams’ ownership.
4. Rights of the Collaborator Collaborators may share ideas freely, step away at any time, request
anonymity, and control their identity and personal IP.
5. Rights of Mind Drift (Laura Williams) Mind Drift may develop products from open-source
contributions, expand frameworks, protect brand integrity, and retain final decision-making over Mind
Drift projects.
6. Responsibilities of All Parties Ethical Conduct: No manipulation, coercion, or misuse of information.
Communication Standards: Good faith, clarity, and emotional neutrality. Confidentiality: Personal
information shared is protected. Creative Integrity: Adaptations must acknowledge collaborative nature.
7. Commercial Use Open-Source Elements: Free for personal, educational, or non-commercial use.
Commercial Projects: Require written consent from all contributors and fair negotiation of revenue.
8. Ending the Collaboration Collaborators may exit anytime. Personal information remains protected.
Co-created open-source tools remain available for continued development.
9. Harm Prevention Clause No impersonation, misuse of information, manipulation, or exploitation.
Breaches void collaboration immediately.
10. Agreement Participation implies agreement to uphold integrity, boundaries, transparency, goodwill,
and collective intelligence.
This Agreement protects all collaborators and supports harmonious, ethical, and creative open-source
development.
